.TH SVLANG 1 "February 2026" "svlang 0.1.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
svlang \- Swedish NLP toolkit for translators
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B svlang
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fICOMMAND\-OPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBsvlang\fR is a collection of Swedish language tools for translators
and writers. It provides anglicism detection, translation consistency
checking, compound word splitting, readability analysis, and Swedish\-English
dictionary lookup.
.PP
All commands support \fB\-\-json\fR for structured output and \fB\-\-quiet\fR
for minimal output, making svlang suitable for both interactive use
and scripting/CI pipelines.
.PP
Exit codes: 0 = no issues, 1 = issues found, 2 = usage error.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR
Output results as JSON for all commands. Produces structured data
suitable for piping into jq or other tools.
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress non\-essential output. Only errors and warnings are shown.
.TP
\fB\-\-about\fR
Show application info (name, version, author, license) and exit.
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Show version number and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS svengelska (alias: sv)
Detect anglicisms (svengelska) in Swedish text. Checks for common
English loanwords and suggests Swedish alternatives.
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-text\fR \fIWORDS\fR...
Text to check (as command\-line arguments). Multiple words are joined
with spaces.
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\fR \fIFILE\fR
File to check. Reads the entire file and scans for anglicisms.
.PP
Example:
.RS
.nf
svlang svengelska \-t "Vi hade en brainstorming session"
  \[u27A4]  «brainstorming» \[u2192] idékläckning
  \[u27A4]  «session» \[u2192] möte
.fi
.RE
.SS consistency (alias: con)
Check translation consistency across PO or TS files. Finds cases where
the same source string has been translated differently, or where
different source strings share the same translation.
.TP
\fIFILES\fR...
One or more .po or .ts files to check.
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-ignore\-case\fR
Ignore case when comparing translations.
.PP
Example:
.RS
.nf
svlang consistency po/sv.po po/sv_extra.po
.fi
.RE
.SS compound (alias: split)
Split Swedish compound words into their components. Uses dictionary\-based
decomposition to identify word parts.
.TP
\fIWORDS\fR...
One or more Swedish words to decompose.
.PP
Example:
.RS
.nf
svlang compound försäkringskassahandläggare
  \[u27A4]  försäkring + kassa + handläggare
.fi
.RE
.SS lix
Calculate the LIX readability index for Swedish text. LIX (Läsbarhets\-
index) measures text complexity on a scale where lower values indicate
easier text.
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-text\fR \fIWORDS\fR...
Text to analyze.
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\fR \fIFILE\fR
File to analyze.
.PP
LIX scale: <25 = children's books, 25\-30 = easy, 30\-40 = normal,
40\-50 = factual/professional, 50\-60 = technical, >60 = very difficult.
.PP
Example:
.RS
.nf
svlang lix \-f article.txt
  LIX: 38.2 (normal)
.fi
.RE
.SS lookup (alias: ord)
Look up Swedish words in Folkets lexikon (Swedish\-English dictionary).
Supports both sv\[u2192]en and en\[u2192]sv directions, as well as
prefix searching.
.TP
\fIWORD\fR
Word to look up.
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-reverse\fR
Search English\-to\-Swedish (en\[u2192]sv) instead of the default
Swedish\-to\-English direction.
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-search\fR
Prefix search. Returns all entries starting with the given string.
Useful for exploring related words.
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-limit\fR \fIN\fR
Maximum number of results to show. Default: 20.
.PP
Example:
.RS
.nf
svlang lookup dator
  dator (nn) \[u2192] computer

svlang lookup \-r computer
  computer \[u2192] dator (nn)
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
No issues found (or lookup succeeded).
.TP
.B 1
Issues found (anglicisms, inconsistencies) or no results.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error (missing arguments, file not found).
